# English Language Policy

All project-facing and client-facing files must use English for names and visible text.

Chat replies are the only exception: follow `.cursor/rules/chat-response-style.mdc`.

## Scope

This rule applies to:
- Generated report files: `*.txt`, `*.md`, `*.html`, and `*.pdf`.
- Portfolio commentary, stress commentary, weights summaries, IPS summaries, comparison notes, and dashboard/report prose.
- Documentation, Cursor rules, prompts/commands, descriptions, headings, labels, chart captions, table labels, and status messages.
- Any new or updated explanatory text in config examples, README/SPEC/docs files, and report builders.
- New file and directory names, unless they are external inputs, existing project paths, ticker symbols, or explicitly requested otherwise.

## Requirements

- Use clear professional English for all visible text.
- Do not introduce Russian text, mixed-language prose, or mojibake in generated artifacts.
- Translate existing Russian-facing wording when touching related files or report-generation logic.
- Keep internal identifiers, ticker symbols, code symbols, JSON keys, and file names unchanged unless the task explicitly asks to rename them.
- Preserve quoted source data as-is only when it is factual input that must remain unchanged; provide the surrounding explanation in English.

## Output Checks

Before considering report or documentation work complete:
- Confirm generated PDFs and text reports contain English visible text.
- Confirm headings, labels, captions, and descriptions are English.
- Confirm no stale instruction still permits Russian output for the touched workflow.
